-- Latvian President Berzins Earned $679,000 Last Year, Leta Says
-- B y   A a r o n   E g l i t i s
-- 2012-04-13T13:30:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-13/latvian-president-berzins-earned-679-000-last-year-leta-says.html
Latvian President Andris Berzins
reported 360,758 lati ($679,000) in income last year, including
interest income and profit on bond and real estate transactions,
 Leta  reported today, citing an official declaration.  Berzins received about 25,000 lati in salary and got 55,000
lati in pension payments for previous work at a  state bank , Leta
reported. Income from selling bonds was 310,789 euros ($409,000)
and he increased the number of properties he owns to 40 from 37,
the Riga-based newswire reported.  The average gross wage in  Latvia  in 2011 was 464 lati a
month, the central statistics office  said  March 2.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aaron Eglitis in Riga at 
 aeglitis@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
